  month = {jul},
  note = {Draft: 27 July 2009.},
  abstract = {There are few areas of modern life in which software is not an important
	(though often invisible) component. The software in our lives is
	increasingly complex; its interaction with the real world means that
	its requirements are in a state of constant change (Lehman & Fern\'andez-Ramil,
	2006). Many non-software products and services, from healthcare to
	transport, education to business, depend on reliable, high-quality
	software.


	Software engineering is the activity that applies engineering principles
	to software. It applies systematic, rigorous discipline to the design
	and development of software, much as civil engineering does to construction.
	Software engineering improves the quality, reliability and predictability
	of software systems, by generating knowledge, tools and processes
	that both facilitate and improve the software development process.
