  year = {2007},
  month = aug,
  abstract = {Conversational recommender systems have recently emerged as useful
	alternative strategies to their single-shot counterpart, especially
	given their ability to expose a user's current preferences. These
	systems use conversational feedback to hone in on the most suitable
	item for recommendation by improving the mechanism that finds useful
	collaborators. We propose a novel architecture for performing recommendation
